  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AL-02 sensitivity gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across all five flow-speed operating points; a screening sensitivity study was conducted internally to rank input contributions to hemolysis index variance, and findings are summarised in the UQ report narrative. All 13 credibility factors have been assessed and the package decision is Accepted. Model Risk Level 5 drives the highest required gradations; achieved levels meet or exceed requirements in each factor following remediation of previously identified gaps.",
