      "name": "Normalised index of haemolysis bench comparison across 5 operating points",
      "description": "NIH values from in-vitro roller pump and centrifugal pump hemolysis experiments compared to model-predicted hemolysis index using the Giersiepen power-law model. Predictions fall within the 95% Monte Carlo prediction interval at all five operating points. UQ report notes that a screening sensitivity study was performed to identify dominant input parameters; shear exposure time and power-law exponent were identified as top contributors in the narrative, though structured linkage to a formal sensitivity analysis artefact was deferred pending tool qualification."
    },
