      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must be under configuration management with documented V&V test suite; all simulation scripts version-controlled and traceable to submitted results.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 deployed under ISO 9001-compliant QMS. Simulation scripts archived in Git repository with SHA-tagged releases. Automated regression test suite covering 47 benchmark cases executed prior to submission. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4 for MRL 5 Class III device."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations via manufactured solution or equivalent benchmark with documented convergence rates.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to Navier-Stokes solver confirming second-order spatial convergence. Hemolysis power-law source term verified against analytical integral for simple Couette flow. Code verification report reviewed by independent analyst. Achieved level 4 satisfies requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index or equivalent must be reported for all primary QoIs; GCI must be below 5% on hemolysis-weighted shear stress.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh GCI study yields GCI_fine = 2.3% on hemolysis-weighted shear stress and 1.8% on pressure rise. Apparent order 1.87 consistent with second-order scheme. Production mesh contains 14.2 million hexahedral cells. Discretization error is bounded and within acceptance threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must be documented with measurement uncertainty; boundary conditions in validation model must reproduce experimental set-points within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental conditions documented per ASTM F1841. Flow rate set-points controlled to ±0.05 L/min; rotational speed to ±5 rpm. CFD boundary conditions replicate experimental set-points; inlet turbulence intensity estimated from upstream piping geometry. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative metric (e.g., E% or validation uncertainty Uval) must be computed for each QoI; comparison must account for both experimental and numerical uncertainties.",
      "rationale": "Validation metric E% computed for NIH at all five operating points; Uval calculated per ASME V&V 20 combining experimental measurement uncertainty and numerical discretization error. Maximum E% = 18.4% at lowest flow condition; all points within expanded validation uncertainty interval. Achieved level 4 satisfies requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (hemolysis index) must be directly validated; secondary QoIs (velocity, pressure) must support confidence in hemolysis prediction pathway.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index is the primary regulatory QoI and is directly compared to bench measurements. Velocity field and pressure rise validated as intermediate QoIs supporting the shear-stress pathway to hemolysis. QoI relevance mapping documented in credibility plan. Achieved level 4 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, operating conditions, and fluid properties must be sufficiently similar to COU to support extrapolation; any gaps must be documented and bounded.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump, which shares impeller topology with the subject VAD. Operating range (2000–3500 rpm, 3–7 L/min) overlaps COU envelope. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water) used in bench study; viscosity matched to 37°C whole blood. Geometric and operating condition similarity assessed as high. Achieved level 4 satisfies requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence must be demonstrated; residuals must drop at least four orders of magnitude and key QoI monitors must reach steady state.",
      "rationale": "All simulations converged to residual levels below 1e-6 for continuity and momentum. Hemolysis index monitor showed variation below 0.1% over final 500 iterations. Double-precision arithmetic employed throughout. Solver error contribution to total numerical uncertainty estimated as negligible relative to discretization error."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup must be independently reviewed; boundary condition and material property inputs must be traceable to approved data sources.",
      "rationale": "Independent analyst performed setup review against approved simulation plan prior to production runs. Boundary conditions and fluid properties traceable to calibrated measurement records and published literature values. No setup errors identified during review. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive model selections must be justified by literature evidence and sensitivity to model form alternatives must be discussed.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published benchmark studies for rotating blood-contacting devices demonstrating superior performance over k-epsilon variants. Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model adopted; Lagrangian particle tracking used for exposure time integration. Alternative model form (Bludszuweit stress-based model) compared qualitatively in validation report; differences within experimental scatter. Model form uncertainty acknowledged in UQ report narrative alongside the screening sensitivity study findings."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs must be characterised with probability distributions; Monte Carlo propagation must be performed and prediction intervals reported for primary QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Eleven uncertain input parameters identified including power-law coefficients (alpha, beta), blood viscosity at operating temperature, inlet turbulence intensity, and pump surface roughness. Distributions assigned from literature meta-analysis and calibration data. 5000-sample Monte Carlo propagation performed; 95% prediction intervals on NIH reported at all five operating points. The UQ report narrative describes a screening sensitivity study that identified shear exposure time and the power-law exponent as dominant variance contributors, supporting the adequacy of the distributional assumptions adopted for these parameters. Achieved level 4 meets required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental sample size must be sufficient to characterise biological and run-to-run variability; repeat measurements must be reported.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis bench experiments conducted in triplicate at each of five operating points using three separate pump units (n=9 per condition). Coefficient of variation across replicates ranged from 6% to 14%. Sample size deemed adequate for characterising run-to-run variability at the required credibility level. Achieved level 3 satisfies requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Input parameters used in COU simulations must correspond to or be demonstrably conservative relative to those used in validated model; any extrapolation must be bounded.",
      "rationale": "COU simulation inputs for blood viscosity, density, and operating speed fall within the validated parameter space. Power-law coefficients are identical between validation and COU runs. Geometric differences between FDA generic pump and subject VAD impeller are within the similarity bounds documented in the relevance assessment. No extrapolation beyond validated input ranges identified. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    }
